&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Topstep is looking for an Engineering Manager to lead a team within &lt;strong&gt;Trading Platform&lt;/strong&gt;, the organization that builds and runs TopstepX. The platform spans order flow and execution, market data, and the services and integrations behind them — real-time systems thousands of funded traders rely on every day, where availability, performance, and correctness matter. This is a people-leadership role: you&#39;ll be accountable for your team&#39;s reliability, quality, and delivery, and for the health and day-to-day running of the team itself — partnering with senior engineers, other engineering leads, Product, and operations. Occasional hands-on work is welcome but isn&#39;t expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run the Team:&lt;/strong&gt; set direction and standards, set the hiring bar and run the interview process to keep the team well-staffed, plan capacity, and shape how it operates day to day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and Develop the Team:&lt;/strong&gt; run 1:1s, real-time feedback, and performance reviews; coach engineers toward individualized growth and address performance issues early; build a culture of psychological safety, transparency, agency, and high standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Reliability and Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; be accountable for the availability, performance, and resilience of the team&#39;s systems and for its engineering process, on-call health, incident follow-through, and observability and tooling (APM, tracing, synthetic/health checks).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; be accountable for the team&#39;s delivery cadence and outcomes, and influence the roadmap to include the technical-investment and reliability work the systems need.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner across the Org:&lt;/strong&gt; collaborate as a peer with the team&#39;s senior engineers and other engineering leads; work with Product, peer Engineering Managers, and operations and infrastructure partners; and keep leadership informed on progress, risks, and trade-offs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications and Key Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7 + years of software engineering experience, including production systems, integrations, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 + years of engineering management experience — hiring, setting direction, coaching, and developing engineers across levels (with clear examples of their growth), and shaping how a team operates and delivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of delivering complex technical work at quality, balancing feature delivery against reliability and technical investment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading teams that own production systems — on-call, incident response, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of building inclusive, collaborative cultures grounded in psychological safety, agency, and continuous learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical credibility to guide architecture and trade-off decisions for backend and distributed systems — ideally high-availability, real-time, or event-driven services and API integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on background with .NET/C# and distributed systems, plus AWS and containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication across technical and non-technical audiences; able to advocate for the team&#39;s needs and work well with peers across engineering and the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A data-informed approach to team health, delivery, and reliability, with good judgment about what to measure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable leading through shifting priorities and balancing the team&#39;s capacity against what the business needs

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Expert Technical Governance &amp;amp; Operational Readiness Manager, you will be the technical execution lead for our IT governance, risk, and readiness frameworks, specifically scoped to protect and empower our Engineering, Technical Program Office, and Trust &amp;amp; Resilience organizations. We are looking for a builder who can own the entire lifecycle of technical compliance, from mapping technical frameworks and implementing lightweight IT workflows to driving continuous audit readiness and implementing automated monitoring. While embedded directly within the Trust &amp;amp; Resilience team, this role maintains a strategic dotted-line reporting relationship to the Chief Compliance Officer to ensure enterprise-wide alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap &amp;amp; Framework Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Translate and execute the technical tracks of the IT governance roadmap, ensuring Product, Engineering, and Trust team operations align with firm policies and external requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Control Framework Mapping:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish and maintain a unified control framework that explicitly maps Topstep’s technical architecture, cloud infrastructure, and technical architecture to established governance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy Architecture &amp;amp; Lifecycle Governance:&lt;/strong&gt; Centralize, maintain, and operationalize a comprehensive technical procedures and documentation library based on policies established and authorized by the Chief Compliance Officer. Manage the technical review, attestation, and exception tracking processes for all engineering and technical partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit Readiness &amp;amp; Evidence Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; Architect, launch, and manage an end-to-end, continuous audit readiness program. Partner with internal audit, enterprise compliance, and our product &amp;amp; engineering teams to replace point-in-time compliance checks with automated, real-time evidence collection pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Escalation &amp;amp; Subject Matter Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as the primary Individual Contributor (IC) and core escalation point for all technical governance queries, translating abstract framework criteria into concrete requirements for product and infrastructure engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications and Key Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 + years of progressive experience in IT GRC, IT audit, or technical compliance within high-growth fintech, SaaS, or highly regulated technology environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable track record of project-level ownership, specifically proving you can implement and scale technical control frameworks, readiness roadmaps, and automated evidence gathering in an immature program environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep working knowledge of core security and governance frameworks, including SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27701/27001, NIST CSF, and financial sector regulatory standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical tooling expertise with modern, cloud-native GRC platforms (e.g., Vanta, Drata, Anecdotes, or LogicGate), including hands-on experience configuring API integrations for continuous control monitoring and automated evidence gathering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering literacy necessary to speak the same language as Cloud Infrastructure and Product Engineering teams; ability to evaluate development/deployment pipelines, system architecture, and access controls for compliance risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomy and execution depth to independently manage complex, cross-functional compliance initiatives from conception to execution without requiring daily managerial direction.&lt;/li&gt;
